(4) Home state means (a) with respect to a state chartered bank, the
state in which the bank is chartered and (b) with respect to a national bank,
the state in which the main office of the bank is located;

(5) Home state regulator means, with respect to an out-of-state state
chartered bank, the bank supervisory agency of the state in which such bank
is chartered;
